[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

A perfect Michaels example; 5-5 in the Majors and 9 points. You bid 2\D and partner says 2\S.  

You have a rather minimum Michaels type hand and you asked partner to choose a Major suit. He chose \Ss. But don't start thinking about what great support you have for his \S suit, he doesn't <b>HAVE</b> a \S suit, he is just supporting yours. In other words, you pass.}

